description:
&lt;p&gt;This locum post is part of a team of 17 Consultants, supported by 10 middle grades and 16 juniors. The post is for 6 months initially to cover gaps created due to pressure from the COVID Pandemic but may be extended. Experience in general paediatrics and neonatology is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointee will take part in the Consultant of the Week rota for the general paediatric ward, and Neonatal Unit, outpatient clinics and a common on-call service for general and neonatal paediatrics. The job is based at Wexham Park Hospital and comes with an office and secretarial support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The on-call consultant is supported by a registrar and 2 juniors at night, and 2 registrars and 3 juniors during the day and at weekends. To support the middle grade rota the post has a weekly evening shift. This post is full time (10 PAs) but candidates wishing to work less are also invited to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Rekha Sanghavi, Chief of Service - Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rekha.sanghavi@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
